{
  "_comment": "Composed wave 5 — application-service/apigateway + compute/scf closure 2026-06-13. gen-wave5-apigw-policy rides the VALIDATED apigw-api chain (gen-wave-apigw 20/20 green) and adds the id-bound GET leftovers + deleteresourcepolicy. gen-wave5-apigw-privatelink is the self-contained privatelink chain: own vpc/subnet (10.163.0.0/20 — unused block) -> networking privatelink-service (AUTO approval, IP type, UNPROVEN docs DTO) -> apigw privatelink-endpoint family AND the scf privatelink-endpoint family against the SAME provider service (one infra chain, all UNPROVEN privatelink risk isolated here; split into a 4th id if the owner prefers). gen-wave5-scf-triggers: apigateway trigger against our own apigw api/stage (verbatim ApigatewayTriggerCreateRequest), listtriggers with the required cloud_function_id query, codes/file + logs/metrics probes. DTOs verbatim from data/api_docs.json; quirks honoured: trigger DELETE needs json {cloud_function_id, trigger_type in [cron, apigateway]} (run 27417986669), scf privatelink-SERVICE enable strands the function in Creating (only disable=false probed), every scf config write flips Deploying -> READY re-poll before the next write/delete.",
  "lifecycles": [
    {
      "id": "gen-wave5-apigw-policy",
      "service": "application-service/apigateway",
      "enabled": true,
      "_note": "Closes the apigw GET leftovers (showresource/listmethods/showmethod/showstage/listreports/showauth/showaccesscontrol/showusageplan/listapikeys) + deleteresourcepolicy on our own api. Every create body is the VALIDATED gen-wave-apigw shape; the resource-policy document is the proven setresourcepolicy shape from apigateway-api-write-coverage, srn pointed at THIS api. listreports allows 400 — docs model has no params but the apigw-api node note suspects a required period query (R3).",
      "steps": [
        {
          "name": "create-api",
          "service": "apigateway",
          "method": "POST",
          "path": "/v1/apis",
          "json": {
            "name": "regrw5api{ualpha}",
            "description": "API regression wave5 policy",
